I am a PhD student in Developmental and Motivational Psychology at Ghent University in Belgium, within [the faculty of Psychology and Educational Sciences](https://www.ugent.be/pp/nl
) at the [department of Developmental, Personality and Social Psychology](https://www.vopspsy.ugent.be/nl/). My [research](https://www.antoinesoetewey.com/research/) interest focuses on the proactive capacity of self-motivation: ÔHow do people motivate themselves?Õ. 

I graduated in (Experimental) Psychology and Statistical Data Analysis. Thereby, I like to read and write about statistics, especially in the software R. Consequently, I wrote a website [CaviR statistics](www.cavirstatistics.com
) and several application to help people in their analyses and to make statistics more applicable.

In my spare time, I attempt to compose music and do photography.
